    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Based on commentary around reddit / twitter / forums, the most pressing questions. These are basically expansions on the bullet points listed in # 5 of OP. \r\n\r\n1. What will be done for EIP 1283?\r\n    - Recommended reading/commenting before the call: https://ethereum-magicians.org/t/remediations-for-eip-1283-reentrancy-bug/2434/7\r\n\r\n2. Timeline for new fork?\r\n     - I personally strongly recommend picking a date on this call, based on what is determined in point 1\r\n     - Most armchair estimates range between 2-6 weeks\r\n     - If devs could be fairly explicit in the things that affect this timeline, would help on comms side, especially if timeline is longer rather than shorter (e.g. tests need to be re-written, testnets need to be dealt with, etc.)\r\n\r\n3. How did this happen? Why wasn't it detected sooner?\r\n    - Who is owning creation of a more thorough retrospective? Timeline? Where can people contribute?\r\n    - Can be very brief, or can be more in depth on call and discuss the good/bad/ugly of what happened. \r\n     - Request for comments on any things that should be included in retrospective (general or specific)\r\n     - https://github.com/ethereum-cat-herders/hard-fork-checklist/issues/1\r\n\r\n4. Testnet plan\r\n    - There has been a surprising amount of commentary on this",
